My meme

(This R markdown file is for my stats220 project 1, the PNG picture is the car named FD2, it is Honda civic Type R from Japanese, my dream car.)

library(magick)

#Read original image
original_image <- image_read("https://i.pinimg.com/736x/e2/f5/56/e2f5566105eb3dd70fb9ca0ebe4430f8--facebook-instagram-memes.jpg")

#create blank image
blank_image <- image_blank(width = 800, height = 600, color = "white")

#add text in blank image
text_image <- image_annotate(image = blank_image, text = "FD2", location = "+90+90", size = 80)

#add text in original image
meme_image <- original_image %>%
  image_append(text = "That moment\nwhen your code\nfinally works", location = "+50+50", size = 30)

#take original image and text image together
final_image <- meme_image %>%
  image_append(stack = text_image, align = "center")

#save final image
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

(This R markdown file is for my stats220 project 1, the gif is the car named FD2, it is Honda civic Type R from Japanese, my dream car.) 

library(magick)

# 1st frame
frame1 <- image_animate(image1, fps = 10, dispose = "previous")

# 2nd frame
frame2 <- image2 %>%
  image_resize("50%") %>%
  image_rotate(45) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Frame 2", location = "+100+100", size = 30)

# 3rd frame
frame3 <- image3 %>%
  image_resize("50%") %>%
  image_flip()

# 4th frame
frame4 <- image4 %>%
  image_modulate(brightness = 80, saturation = 80) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Frame 4", location = "+100+100", size = 30)

# take 4 frames together
animation <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4) %>%
  image_animate(fps = 10)

# save gif
image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
